org.gradoop.flink.model.impl.operators.grouping

Class GroupingGroupReduce<G extends GraphHead,V extends Vertex,E extends Edge,LG extends BaseGraph<G,V,E,LG,GC>,GC extends BaseGraphCollection<G,V,E,LG,GC>>

    public class GroupingGroupReduce<G extends GraphHead,V extends Vertex,E extends Edge,LG extends BaseGraph<G,V,E,LG,GC>,GC extends BaseGraphCollection<G,V,E,LG,GC>>
extends Grouping<G,V,E,LG,GC>
    Grouping implementation that uses group + groupReduce for building super vertices and updating the original vertices. Algorithmic idea: 1) Map vertices to a minimal representation, i.e. VertexGroupItem. 2) Group vertices on label and/or property. 3) Create a super vertex id for each group and collect a non-candidate VertexGroupItem for each group element and one additional super vertex tuple that holds the group aggregate. 4) Filter output of 3) a) non-candidate tuples are mapped to VertexWithSuperVertex b) super vertex tuples are used to build final super vertices 5) Map edges to a minimal representation, i.e. EdgeGroupItem 6) Join edges with output of 4a) and replace source/target id with super vertex id. 7) Updated edges are grouped by source and target id and optionally by label and/or edge property. 8) Group combine on the workers and compute aggregate. 9) Group reduce globally and create final super edges.
